Santiago Vergini is keen to stay at Sunderland if the club stay in the Premier League . 
  The defender played a key role in Sunderland's 1-0 derby win over Newcastle United on Sunday . 
  The 26-year-old returned to the club on a season-long loan in August . 
  He has indicated he is ready to extend his stay at the Stadium of Light . 
  Premier League survival could trigger a two-year permanent deal . 
 